description:
Ink on canvas. 2013.
Original work signed by the artist.

Size:
Unframed: 91.5 x 91.5 cm (36 x 36 ins)
Framed: 94 x 94 cm (37 x 37 ins)

We offer a bespoke framing service.
Ian's work is framed in an unglazed tray frame.

Please allow an additional two weeks for framing.

Prices include postage & packing using a 'Signed For Service' to the UK only.

We are happy to ship internationally.
Please contact us for shipping costs to other countries before you buy.

About Ian Mason

We say: Ian Mason studied Fine Art (Sculpture) at Newcastle Poly and completed a PGDip In Interior Design at the University of Brighton. He now lives and works In Devon. Ian regularly exhibits with the US gallery Dogartdealer and his work is in private collections In the UK, Europe and the US.
 
The Artist says:
I work a lot from found Images - old books, magazines and photographs or stills from video footage. My work often involves showing the process of 'making'. I work in one sitting to achieve this freshness; capturing the image with a simple glimpse or outline. I reinforce this with my choice of materials, reducing the work to monochrome and highlighting areas of shape and form. Minimal treatment of the canine subject maybe, but I'm a strong believer that less is more.

Ian also works to commission. Please contact us for details.

About Jane-Charlotte Jones

We say: Jane-Charlotte studied Fine Art at the Byam Shaw School of Art in London and graduated from the Corcoran School of Art in Washington DC in 1994. She lived and worked in New York City for 15 years creating portraits, murals and bespoke painted furniture. She has exhibited in the US and Canada and is now working in the UK.

When I was growing up I wanted to be a mermaid or an astronaut. But I had to settle for the next best thing - being an artist. Inspired by the myriad of dogs I'd meet on my travels in NYC  - and much to the chagrin of my rabbits - I began creating paintings that showed them in all their active, joyful, individual glory.

name: The Enlightened Hound / Linoprints
description:
The Enlightened Hound typographic prints celebrate the instinctive principles dogs follow for a simple and contented life. 

There are five prints in the series. They work beautifully as a collection or as a single print and make a perfect gift for dog owners. 

The designs are also available as greeting cards in our Essentials department.

The prints have been created using authentic fonts from original Wild West and US Civil War posters. The letters are hand carved onto lino printing plates, then each poster is individually hand-printed on acid free archival 170gsm printmaking paper with traditional linseed oil inks, using hand-mixed colours, inspired by the American Colonial era.

Each print uses four different lino plates and three colours to produce. Each plate/colour is printed separately by hand.

The vintage style, slightly distressed lettering and the typographical style is reminiscent of old Wild West Wanted Posters and 19th century American Show Posters.

Prints are signed and editioned in sets of 250 - each edition uses a different unique colour combination.
Paper size: 400 x 500 mm
Image size: 276 x 397 mm

The work of The Enlightened Hound (aka artist Debbie Kendall) is inspired by her Portuguese Water Dog Figo.

Our shipping costs are to the UK only.

We are happy to ship internationally.
Please contact us for shipping costs to other countries before you buy.

The Enlightened Hound cards celebrate the instinctive principles dogs follow for a simple and contented life.

The set of four cards have been recreated from The Enlightened Hound's original linoprints using authentic fonts from original Wild West and US Civil War posters. The letters are softly distressed to enhance the vintage feel of the cards.

The cards are printed in the UK on a high quality 275gsm textured matt card, using vegetable based inks and are blank inside for your own message.

Each card is individually sealed in its own cellophane bag with a yellow envelope.

The work of The Enlightened Hound (aka artist Debbie Kendall) is inspired by her Portuguese Water Dog Figo. A selection of the limited edition linoprints are available in our Art department.

Our shipping costs are to the UK only.

We are happy to ship internationally.
Please contact us for shipping costs to other countries before you buy.
